  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Duty Engineer",
  "description": "<ul><li>Ensure the efficient, economical and sound operation of equipment i.e. Boiler, Chiller, Emergency Generators, Fire Pumps, Kitchen, Refrigeration, HVAC/Laundry and the auxiliaries of these, etc.</li><li>Ensure immediate provision of services necessary to guests and other operating departments.</li><li>Ensure coordination with other operating departments in the implementation of repair and maintenance schedule.</li><li>Responsible for engineering and maintenance operations of the hotel, hotel property, restaurant and grounds.</li><li>Respond to engineering and maintenance concerns.</li><li>Perform and/or monitors maintenance and preventive maintenance projects.</li><li>Respond to all building related safety concerns.</li><li>Maintain departmental compliance with hotel maintenance procedures.</li><li>Support hotel departmental maintenance programs and executes daily, weekly and monthly checklist.</li><li>Assist management in specifying proper supplies and equipment for operations.</li><li>Deal with guest related concerns.</li><li>Maintain the guest room, public space, and back of the hotel areas in good repair by performing various tasks related to a variety of trades including carpentry, plumbing, electrical, air conditioning, painting, wall covering and tiling to ensure an attractive and well-maintained hotel.</li><li>Must possess knowledgeable of basic hand/power tool operation.</li></ul>",
